1
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:11,567
<i>- Just leave it there.
- Where am I going to put this?</i>

2
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:13,900
<i>There's still some more.
This is delicious.</i>

3
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:16,300
<i>Sir, there's something
on your...</i>

4
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:20,500
<i> I think that's Lee and Bal.</i>

5
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:21,967
<i> What do you need?</i>

6
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:24,867
<i>Why are you carrying a suitcase,
and what help do you need?</i>

7
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,300
<i> I haven't been able to work</i>

8
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:29,600
<i>because I'm busy being a witness
in Amo's case.</i>

9
00:00:29,733 --> 00:00:32,233
<i> Maybe I could stay here?</i>

10
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:33,367
<i> I'm sorry...</i>

11
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:35,400
<i>Selena, it's a good thing
that you came here.</i>

12
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:38,767
<i>You know that Sir Tonyo
won't refuse you.</i>

13
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,533
<i> Bobby...</i>

14
00:00:40,667 --> 00:00:42,633
<i> Bobby's job is hard, right?</i>

15
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,533
<i>Especially when they conduct
a police operation.</i>

16
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:47,200
<i>One of her feet is in the grave.</i>

17
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:48,800
<i> Oh my, it's scary.</i>

18
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:52,333
<i>That's why it's better if you
don't prolong the fights,</i>

19
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:55,100
<i>especially with the ones
you love, right?</i>

20
00:00:55,233 --> 00:00:56,000
<i> Yes.</i>

21
00:00:56,133 --> 00:00:57,867
<i> I have something to tell you.</i>

22
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,067
<i>You already know that your
mother was rejected by the man</i>

23
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,300
<i> who got her pregnant?</i>

24
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:03,633
<i> Yes, Grandmother. Why?</i>

25
00:01:03,767 --> 00:01:07,567
<i>Because the one who got her
pregnant was Mayor Guerrero!</i>

26
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:12,500
That's why
I'm so angry with him.

27
00:01:13,067 --> 00:01:14,833
I want to protect you.

28
00:01:18,067 --> 00:01:19,767
Forgive me, Bobby.

29
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:21,433
I hid it from you.

30
00:01:29,067 --> 00:01:29,667
Grandmother...

31
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:33,033
I need to talk to him.

32
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,400
Oh, Sir Tonyo, good morning!

33
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,300
Why are you wearing
Lara's clothes?

34
00:02:15,467 --> 00:02:16,833
Oh, yes.

35
00:02:16,967 --> 00:02:18,767
I saw them in the closet.

36
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:21,733
Well, they fit me.
So I borrowed it.

37
00:02:22,133 --> 00:02:22,733
Is it okay?

38
00:02:23,267 --> 00:02:24,100
It looks good on me, right?

39
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,000
Okay, okay. It's fine.

40
00:02:30,367 --> 00:02:31,567
By the way, Selena...

41
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:33,600
I have work.

42
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,233
What time are you coming home?

43
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:38,567
Why?

44
00:02:38,933 --> 00:02:42,400
So I can make you some dinner.

45
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:47,700
Oh, no need. Don't bother.

46
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:49,533
By the way...

47
00:02:50,067 --> 00:02:52,133
there's food in the fridge.

48
00:02:52,267 --> 00:02:54,067
If you get hungry,
you can help yourself.

49
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,933
By the way,

50
00:02:56,067 --> 00:02:57,700
what kind of job
are you looking for?

51
00:02:57,833 --> 00:03:00,267
I can help you find one,

52
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:03,700
so you can also find
a place to live.

53
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:09,267
Sir, it seems like you're
already kicking me out.

54
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,433
I just got here.

55
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:12,800
No, it's not like that.

56
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:16,167
Of course, I want to help you
find a job.

57
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:17,567
I know it's hard to lose a job,

58
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:19,167
especially these days.

59
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:23,333
Soon, maybe.

60
00:03:23,467 --> 00:03:26,400
Maybe I can stay here for now.

61
00:03:27,033 --> 00:03:29,967
Well, I'll do everything
you want me to do.

62
00:03:30,100 --> 00:03:32,600
Do you want me to do some
general cleaning later?

63
00:03:33,233 --> 00:03:35,033
Oh, no, no.

64
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:39,800
If possible, please don't touch
the things here too much, okay?

65
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:43,833
And don't forget
to lock the door.

66
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:46,067
Okay.

67
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,333
Okay...

68
00:03:47,967 --> 00:03:49,233
I'll get dressed first.

69
00:03:49,367 --> 00:03:51,800
Oh, wait, is your uniform
already ironed?

70
00:03:52,133 --> 00:03:53,467
I'll iron it, okay?

71
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,567
Okay.

72
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,333
The return of the comeback!

73
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,167
What, Bok?

74
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:18,867
How are you?

75
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,633
Where is Enriquez?

76
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:22,233
Oh, I don't know.

77
00:04:22,533 --> 00:04:23,833
Why? Is she absent?

78
00:04:23,967 --> 00:04:25,900
Hey...

79
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:28,500
You're still acting?

80
00:04:28,667 --> 00:04:31,167
She was with you last night.
Where did you go?

81
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:34,200
No, she doesn't feel well,

82
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:36,300
maybe because of the alcohol
she drank last night.

83
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:38,933
So there, I just took her home.

84
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,767
Wait, wait.

85
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,933
Any update about the guy
we caught last night?

86
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:47,367
Oh, change topic!

87
00:04:47,967 --> 00:04:48,733
Oh, okay, okay.

88
00:04:48,867 --> 00:04:51,267
I'll give in to
your change of topic.

89
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:53,067
Well, Monty, he's in jail now.

90
00:04:53,667 --> 00:04:54,667
Same thing.

91
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,367
We also can't get any
information from him...

92
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:58,633
because he only
gets it from others.

93
00:05:01,833 --> 00:05:03,133
I wonder who his source is?

94
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:05,567
That's what we need to know,

95
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:09,333
and what happened
to you and Enriquez.

96
00:05:09,467 --> 00:05:10,500
- What, Bok?
- Nothing!

97
00:05:10,633 --> 00:05:11,767
I just took her home!

98
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:13,267
- Nothing happened.
- Oh, you took her home.

99
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,733
- And then?
- Oh, nothing!

100
00:05:14,867 --> 00:05:16,200
I brought her home, that's it.

101
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:17,467
I went home after.

102
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:18,533
Yes, Governor.

103
00:05:18,667 --> 00:05:20,133
Okay, I'll take care of it
right away.

104
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,167
Okay, Governor.

105
00:05:23,567 --> 00:05:24,900
Okay, okay, okay.

106
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:26,467
Okay.

107
00:05:27,067 --> 00:05:28,000
Thank you very much.

108
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:29,733
Okay, Governor.
Thank you, thank you.

109
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,100
Mayor, someone is looking
for you...

110
00:05:32,233 --> 00:05:33,233
it's Sergeant Enriquez.

111
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:35,100
Sergeant Enriquez, okay.

112
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:39,367
I hope you're here
to accept my offer

113
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:42,967
to be part of the special task
force of Calabari.

114
00:05:43,233 --> 00:05:46,300
Mayor, I'm not here
to talk about the task force.

115
00:05:46,667 --> 00:05:48,733
Oh, why are you here?

116
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:51,200
Do you know Alicia Enriquez?

117
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:00,800
Yes.

118
00:06:02,067 --> 00:06:04,100
She was the only woman I loved.

119
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,067
At that time,

120
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:11,233
I was willing to give up
everything for her,

121
00:06:11,467 --> 00:06:13,300
including my wife, Sophia.

122
00:06:13,733 --> 00:06:14,767
One day,

123
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:17,967
she suddenly stopped
reaching out to me.

124
00:06:19,267 --> 00:06:20,733
Then I found out...

125
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,567
she had died because...

126
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:25,500
Because of a robber!

127
00:06:27,867 --> 00:06:31,300
<i> Mother! Mother!</i>

128
00:06:33,467 --> 00:06:34,633
<i> Mother!</i>

129
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:37,200
<i> Mother! Help!</i>

130
00:06:37,433 --> 00:06:40,400
I was there when he was robbed
and killed...

131
00:06:41,967 --> 00:06:44,300
because Alicia Enriquez
is my mother.

132
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:49,767
Are you my daughter?

133
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:51,200
Maybe.

134
00:06:54,267 --> 00:06:56,900
But I'm not here because I want
to get something from you.

135
00:06:58,133 --> 00:07:03,533
I'm here to let you know that
Alicia Enriquez has a child.

136
00:07:27,933 --> 00:07:29,267
What, Bok? Nothing yet?

137
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,333
Nothing's happening.

138
00:07:35,267 --> 00:07:37,000
Do you think Monty
is telling the truth?

139
00:07:38,767 --> 00:07:41,900
Monty won't gain anything
by lying to us.

140
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:45,367
In fact, we talked about

141
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:48,067
the possibility that his
sentence could be reduced

142
00:07:48,233 --> 00:07:50,600
if his cooperation
yielded results.

143
00:07:58,867 --> 00:07:59,633
Bok, Bok...

144
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:14,300
Look at that.

145
00:08:26,667 --> 00:08:28,267
Come on, let's follow the van.

146
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,167
Let's go.

147
00:09:04,567 --> 00:09:09,167
Bok, did the white van really
go to the right place?

148
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:12,000
Did it actually come here to the
Calabari State University?

149
00:09:12,133 --> 00:09:16,100
That means the source
is actually there.

150
00:09:44,733 --> 00:09:45,567
Enriquez...

151
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:48,900
can we talk?

152
00:09:49,933 --> 00:09:51,767
Excuse me, Sir.
I have a lot to do.

153
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:53,900
Oh, about...

154
00:09:54,033 --> 00:09:55,133
That's okay, Sir.

155
00:09:55,767 --> 00:09:56,933
There's no problem with that.

156
00:09:57,700 --> 00:09:58,833
I have a lot to do, Sir.

157
00:09:58,967 --> 00:09:59,867
I'm sorry.

158
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:08,067
Oh, why does she look like that?

159
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,967
What happened?

160
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:15,900
Conde, Garcia.

161
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:17,233
Sit down.

162
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:34,167
What do you think is the best
strategy for that?

163
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,500
As for me, Sir,

164
00:10:37,867 --> 00:10:40,733
I don't think we can investigate
the university upfront.

165
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:44,967
Because if they sense it,
it would definitely lie low.

166
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:49,933
The best thing we can do is
assign an undercover agent.

167
00:10:50,367 --> 00:10:52,667
That's right.

168
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:56,000
I've always dreamed
of becoming a professor.

169
00:10:56,767 --> 00:11:01,500
Imagine, Professor Garcia, GMRC.

170
00:11:01,767 --> 00:11:04,367
But, Bok, I think...

171
00:11:04,867 --> 00:11:08,367
it's better if we place an
undercover agent as a student,

172
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:10,500
because that's most likely
where the sale is happening.

173
00:11:13,533 --> 00:11:14,433
Conde is right.

174
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,333
But with those looks,

175
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:21,267
no one will believe
you're a student.

176
00:11:22,167 --> 00:11:27,600
So we need to find a new face
who can pretend to be a student.

177
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:29,300
Okay, Chief, I'll go
look for someone.

178
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:31,367
Okay, you're dismissed.

179
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:32,000
Chief!

180
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,433
Why do we need to look
for someone else?

181
00:11:33,567 --> 00:11:35,033
Why do we need that if I'm here?

182
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:36,933
I was often mistaken
for a 14-year-old

183
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,400
at Miss Fe's eatery...

184
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:02,967
<i> I'm here to inform you...</i>

185
00:12:03,633 --> 00:12:05,867
<i>that Alicia Enriquez
has a child.</i>

186
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:09,300
Alicia...

187
00:12:12,467 --> 00:12:14,833
it turns out
we have a lovechild.

188
00:12:20,767 --> 00:12:22,200
Bobby is my daughter.

189
00:12:27,933 --> 00:12:29,200
Hey, it's still early, and you
guys are gossiping already.

190
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:30,867
- Give me your soft drinks!
- What's with you? This is mine!

191
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,300
- You're shameless and ugly!
- Ugly?

192
00:12:32,433 --> 00:12:33,800
You're chubby, I can't hear you.

193
00:12:34,267 --> 00:12:35,233
What, Bro? How are you?

194
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:36,300
I'll have this.

195
00:12:38,267 --> 00:12:40,167
The politicians we talked to
were all talk and no action.

196
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:41,767
It's just nonsense,
nothing came of it.

197
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:43,400
Look, once they win,
they're gone.

198
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:47,133
That's why we supported
those politicians

199
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:48,867
because they promised us
something.

200
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:51,300
And now that they've won,
they're ignoring us.

201
00:12:51,433 --> 00:12:53,033
- Damn!
- Nothing!

202
00:12:53,667 --> 00:12:54,633
- Damn!
- It's gone.

203
00:12:54,767 --> 00:12:57,267
Bro, what if let's try
to find a way again?

204
00:12:57,733 --> 00:12:58,867
Let's steal a cell phone
so we can...

205
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,133
We don't have any money.

206
00:13:00,267 --> 00:13:02,333
Right, Bro, there's something
going on in the plaza later.

207
00:13:02,467 --> 00:13:04,067
- Let's go? Come with us.
- What, Vince? Come on!

208
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,000
Come on, come on.

209
00:13:05,133 --> 00:13:06,867
Hey, hey! Hey, stop that.

210
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,600
- Why?
- Dude, didn't we agree that

211
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:09,933
we're going to change
our lives, right?

212
00:13:10,067 --> 00:13:10,700
This will be the last one.

213
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:11,600
We don't have any money.

214
00:13:11,733 --> 00:13:13,567
Dude, let's fight fair
and square!

215
00:13:13,933 --> 00:13:15,467
Just because
you look like a criminal

216
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,800
doesn't mean you're going
to do bad things.

217
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:18,133
Vince, you're too harsh.

218
00:13:18,267 --> 00:13:19,233
Isn't it enough that we already
feel bad about ourselves,

219
00:13:19,367 --> 00:13:20,367
and now about the world too?

220
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:21,433
Oh, there's Boss Tonyo.

221
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,633
- Boss!
- Boss Tonyo!

222
00:13:22,767 --> 00:13:23,600
- Blessings will always come.
- Here's Boss Tonyo.

223
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:24,800
Even if you don't pray,
it will come.

224
00:13:24,933 --> 00:13:26,533
- Boss!
- Oh, what do you need?

225
00:13:26,667 --> 00:13:27,467
Nothing hurts.

226
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,767
By the way, Vince...

227
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:30,233
I'm going to ask you
to do some work.

228
00:13:30,367 --> 00:13:31,833
Maybe you can come see me later?

229
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:33,233
- Oh, my...
- What is it, Boss?

230
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:35,367
- Why only Vince?
- Why only him?

231
00:13:35,867 --> 00:13:37,633
Well, you want to steal again,
right?

232
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:39,300
Go ahead, try it if you dare.

233
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:41,100
Oh, he heard you.

234
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,233
- Come see me later, okay?
- Okay, Boss.

235
00:13:44,133 --> 00:13:45,600
Hey, give us a bonus.

236
00:13:45,733 --> 00:13:47,400
Give you a bonus?
I don't know about you two!

237
00:13:47,533 --> 00:13:50,000
If you want to steal,
then go ahead and steal.

238
00:13:50,133 --> 00:13:51,867
Let's pawn your cell phone.

239
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,300
You don't have any load.

240
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:54,733
Yes, Grandmother,

241
00:13:54,900 --> 00:14:00,333
mayor said that mother was the
only one who didn't show up.

242
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:04,900
He said he was ready to leave
his entire family for mother.

243
00:14:05,167 --> 00:14:06,800
You actually believe that?

244
00:14:08,533 --> 00:14:09,467
Yes, Grandmother.

245
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:13,233
Well, it seems like
he's telling the truth.

246
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:17,167
I have a feeling that mother
was the one who stayed away,

247
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:19,633
so she wouldn't interfere
with the mayor's family.

248
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:23,467
What are you going to do now
that you've met your father?

249
00:14:24,867 --> 00:14:26,100
I don't know, Grandmother.

250
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:29,233
I don't know what to feel.

251
00:14:33,533 --> 00:14:35,433
What's important, Grandmother...

252
00:14:36,767 --> 00:14:38,300
is that you've told me
the truth.

253
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:48,367
What's the matter, Boss?

254
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:49,767
Why do you want to talk to me?

255
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:54,667
I know you've been wanting

256
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,400
to change your life
for a long time now.

257
00:14:56,967 --> 00:14:58,233
So I want to help you.

258
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:02,733
I'd like to make you an
undercover at a university.

259
00:15:04,033 --> 00:15:05,400
That is, if you can
actually do it.

260
00:15:05,933 --> 00:15:07,200
Undercover, Boss?

261
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:11,500
Yes, Boss, I can do that.

262
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,533
I'm in, Boss.

263
00:15:13,667 --> 00:15:16,300
Boss, thank you very much.

264
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:18,667
This mission is important.

265
00:15:19,167 --> 00:15:21,967
So you and your partner
must do your best.

266
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:23,800
Partner, Boss?

267
00:15:23,933 --> 00:15:25,567
Who will be my partner, Boss?

268
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:30,300
Lieutenant Antonio Conde,

269
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:32,833
I'm Corporal Wilbert Mariano
reporting for duty, Sir.

270
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:37,967
Mariano...

271
00:15:38,433 --> 00:15:40,100
he will be your partner.

272
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:42,000
This is Vince.

273
00:15:44,133 --> 00:15:45,133
Just call me Will, Bro.

274
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:48,300
I graduated magna cum laude,
BS Criminology.

275
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:49,800
Cool!

276
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:52,233
I'm Vince, Bro.

277
00:15:52,767 --> 00:15:55,000
I graduated from...

278
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:56,667
being a criminal.

279
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:58,500
I'm starting a new life, Bro.

280
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,400
Here.

281
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,833
Study your identities.

282
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,200
Take them to heart.

283
00:16:10,067 --> 00:16:11,867
For people to believe you,

284
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:14,900
you have to be the first
to believe.

285
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:18,500
Yes, Boss, I can do this.

286
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:20,033
You know what,

287
00:16:20,267 --> 00:16:22,633
I was planning to audition
for Starstruck before.

288
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:24,367
But I'm just busy,

289
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:27,433
that's why this is
so easy for me, Boss.

290
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:29,567
Bro...

291
00:16:30,467 --> 00:16:32,967
can we take this
assignment seriously?

292
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:34,367
Why? Do I look like
I'm not serious?

293
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:35,367
Yes,

294
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,200
what we're going into
is not a joke.

295
00:16:37,933 --> 00:16:39,633
So if you're not going
to be serious,

296
00:16:39,767 --> 00:16:41,100
just ask someone to replace you.

297
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:42,233
This guy has an attitude!

298
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:43,833
Can you guys stop that?

299
00:16:45,933 --> 00:16:47,533
That's the first thing
you need to learn...

300
00:16:48,467 --> 00:16:50,933
how to get along as partners.

301
00:16:51,433 --> 00:16:52,867
Because that's the key

302
00:16:53,300 --> 00:16:55,600
to making your mission
successful.

303
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:57,133
Is that clear?

304
00:16:59,867 --> 00:17:00,467
Yes, Sir.

305
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:02,233
Yes, Boss.

306
00:17:03,667 --> 00:17:04,500
So arrogant.

307
00:17:11,967 --> 00:17:13,433
Daddy!

308
00:17:13,567 --> 00:17:15,267
Morning!

309
00:17:15,433 --> 00:17:17,733
- Hi, Dad!
- Hi, Mom.

310
00:17:17,867 --> 00:17:19,733
- Morning.
- Morning.

311
00:17:19,867 --> 00:17:20,900
- Dad.
- Wow!

312
00:17:21,033 --> 00:17:22,800
Come on, sit down, sit down.

313
00:17:24,167 --> 00:17:26,400
I wanted to tell you something.

314
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:30,300
Looks like...

315
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:32,867
it's something serious, Dad.

316
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:33,967
What is it?

317
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:36,233
Yes, Dad, what's going on?

318
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:40,033
I'm going to admit
something to you.

319
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:43,667
Long time ago...

320
00:17:44,967 --> 00:17:46,267
when I was still a councilor...

321
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:50,300
I've cheated on your mother.

322
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:52,167
What?

323
00:17:54,867 --> 00:17:56,300
Your mother knows about this.

324
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:02,233
But that woman is long gone.

325
00:18:03,633 --> 00:18:05,967
She was killed by a robber.

326
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:08,300
And yesterday...

327
00:18:09,733 --> 00:18:10,833
I found out...

328
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:14,400
that I had a child with her.

329
00:18:22,933 --> 00:18:24,433
Our child is...

330
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:28,967
Sergeant Bobby Enriquez.

331
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:31,100
Bobby?

332
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:39,033
I want her to be part
of my life.

333
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:41,833
I would like to make it up
to her.

334
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:45,867
And I hope...

335
00:18:47,567 --> 00:18:48,967
you'll grant my request.

336
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,333
It's all right, Joaquin.

337
00:18:55,767 --> 00:19:00,867
I think the girl deserves to get
to know her father better.

338
00:19:03,567 --> 00:19:05,667
Thank you very much, Sophia.

339
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,600
We shouldn't waste
any more time.

340
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:26,400
We need to get some information.

341
00:19:26,633 --> 00:19:27,900
You know, let's separate.

342
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:29,600
You can ask questions there,
and I'll ask here.

343
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:30,967
Okay, Dude.

344
00:19:31,633 --> 00:19:32,767
See you later.

345
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:55,133
My God, it's so hot.

346
00:19:55,267 --> 00:19:56,300
It's so hot!

347
00:19:56,433 --> 00:19:57,533
I don't know why.

348
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:02,133
You don't have a class?

349
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:04,633
Bro...

350
00:20:04,767 --> 00:20:05,300
- Yes, Bro.
- Can I ask a question?

351
00:20:05,433 --> 00:20:06,167
What is it?

352
00:20:06,767 --> 00:20:09,333
Do you know where
the science club is?

353
00:20:09,467 --> 00:20:10,533
I'm just new here.

354
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:11,867
- I'm sorry.
- Science club?

355
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,067
That's at the end.

356
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:15,767
When you get there,
you'll see a restroom.

357
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:17,733
When you see the restroom,
turn left.

358
00:20:18,233 --> 00:20:19,367
That's where the
science club is.

359
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:20,900
- Okay, Bro, thank you.
- Okay, okay.

360
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:22,133
Be careful, be careful.

361
00:20:28,933 --> 00:20:30,567
Miss, excuse me.

362
00:20:31,367 --> 00:20:35,133
Do you know where the Mass Comm
building is?

363
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:38,667
Go straight there,
then turn left.

364
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,667
When you make a turn,
you'll see...

365
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:43,400
- the building of Mass Comm.
- Thank you.

366
00:20:50,367 --> 00:20:51,133
Glen...

367
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:54,367
what do you think of what
we talked about earlier

368
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,700
at breakfast?

369
00:20:56,033 --> 00:20:59,267
Well, I think,
Sergeant Enriquez would be...

370
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,700
a good addition
to our family.

371
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:04,367
So you don't have
any animosity towards Bobby?

372
00:21:06,333 --> 00:21:07,300
Nothing.

373
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:09,167
This isn't a television series.

374
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:11,633
I'm not going to fight
for the inheritance.

375
00:21:11,767 --> 00:21:12,767
Plus...

376
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:15,600
I'm actually excited
to work with her.

377
00:21:17,467 --> 00:21:19,467
Okay, Glen, I'll go ahead.

378
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,400
- Okay.
- Thanks for dropping me off.

379
00:21:21,533 --> 00:21:22,767
Bye!

380
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:23,667
Take care.

381
00:21:35,433 --> 00:21:36,200
Hey, Bro.

382
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:37,733
What?

383
00:21:38,067 --> 00:21:39,433
Did you get some information?

384
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,133
Nothing, Bro, negative.

385
00:21:42,833 --> 00:21:43,967
It's hard, Bro.

386
00:21:44,100 --> 00:21:46,600
Do we ask them if they
sell beauty products

387
00:21:46,733 --> 00:21:48,133
or pimple patches?

388
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:49,967
There's nothing, Bro.

389
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:52,767
Oh my, you're really foolish.

390
00:21:53,367 --> 00:21:53,967
Let's go.

391
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:03,900
Sir, you requested to see me?

392
00:22:04,167 --> 00:22:05,233
Yes, Enriquez.

393
00:22:05,367 --> 00:22:09,600
Tomorrow, you have to go to
the regional headquarters.

394
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:11,233
What?

395
00:22:11,633 --> 00:22:12,533
Why?

396
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:15,000
For your oathtaking...

397
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:19,833
because you've been promoted
to Master Sergeant.

398
00:22:20,867 --> 00:22:22,067
What?

399
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:24,867
Seriously? Are you serious?

400
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:25,967
Sir, it seems like
she doesn't want it.

401
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:27,600
No, no, Sir! I want it!

402
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:31,200
Congratulations,
Master Sergeant Enriquez.

403
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:33,533
That's because of all the work
you've done on Amo's case,

404
00:22:33,667 --> 00:22:34,433
well-deserved.

405
00:22:34,567 --> 00:22:35,300
Thank you, Sir.

406
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:38,467
Sir, this can only mean
one thing.

407
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:39,667
What?

408
00:22:40,133 --> 00:22:41,933
I'm a good trainer.

409
00:22:43,667 --> 00:22:47,700
Congratulations,
Master Sergeant Enriquez.

410
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:48,733
Thank you, Sir.

411
00:22:50,733 --> 00:22:51,867
You make us proud.

412
00:22:59,633 --> 00:23:01,700
You even wore glasses, Bro.

413
00:23:01,833 --> 00:23:02,800
That's great.

414
00:23:04,067 --> 00:23:05,800
But, Bro, this is exciting
because...

415
00:23:06,267 --> 00:23:08,433
I really wanted to go
to high school before.

416
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:12,933
Keep your eyes sharp.

417
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:17,233
Our goal is to identify the
seller of the pimple patches

418
00:23:17,367 --> 00:23:18,167
at school.

419
00:23:18,933 --> 00:23:20,467
So let's blend in first.

420
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:22,800
It's better for the two of us
to keep a low profile for now.

421
00:23:22,967 --> 00:23:25,067
Why are you so annoying, Ryan?

422
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,900
I said, I don't want you
anymore, okay?

423
00:23:27,033 --> 00:23:29,033
I don't want you anymore.
I'm tired of you.

424
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,500
We can't get involved in that.

425
00:23:32,633 --> 00:23:34,467
But, Bro, a woman is being hurt.

426
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:41,100
Why? Tell me.

427
00:23:41,233 --> 00:23:42,233
Ouch.

428
00:23:42,467 --> 00:23:44,767
Tell me first, go ahead.
Then I'll stop bothering you.

429
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:46,267
It hurts! You're hurting me!

430
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:47,700
- Let me go!
- Oh, what?

431
00:23:48,133 --> 00:23:49,100
You have no reason to say,
right?

432
00:23:49,233 --> 00:23:50,467
Ouch! What's with you?

433
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,867
You really want to get hurt,
don't you?

434
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:54,400
That's enough, Bro.

435
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:56,167
You're hurting a woman.

436
00:23:57,167 --> 00:23:58,133
What do you care?

437
00:23:59,367 --> 00:24:00,233
Do you know him, Jem?

438
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:03,033
She doesn't know you.

439
00:24:04,633 --> 00:24:06,100
If I were you, I wouldn't
interfere in this.

440
00:24:07,033 --> 00:24:08,200
You don't know the person
you're bumping into.

441
00:24:09,733 --> 00:24:11,133
You don't know me either.

442
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:16,900
Are you brave?

443
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:27,167
What?

444
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:31,100
Are you still brave?

445
00:24:39,233 --> 00:24:41,333
We want you to try out
for the taekwondo team.

446
00:24:41,467 --> 00:24:44,267
His sibling got imprisoned
for using illegal substances.

447
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,600
The one that's trending,
the pimple patch drugs.

448
00:24:46,833 --> 00:24:47,833
I'll assign you

449
00:24:47,967 --> 00:24:51,467
to transfer Simon De la Rama
and Amado Tindog

450
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,200
to Calabari State Prison.

451
00:24:53,333 --> 00:24:54,500
Isn't Mandong Warak there?

452
00:24:54,633 --> 00:24:56,067
Who's Mandong Warak?

453
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:57,533
That's a police killer.

454
00:24:57,667 --> 00:25:00,600
His name suits him because
his face was ruined by Tonyo.

455
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:01,833
Get ready, police officers.

456
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:05,633
I'll take you all one by one
until I reach Antonio Conde.

457
00:25:05,767 --> 00:25:06,967
Hold him!

458
00:25:08,333 --> 00:25:09,100
Swimming race,

459
00:25:09,233 --> 00:25:10,500
just like what we used
to do before.

460
00:25:10,633 --> 00:25:11,733
I don't have time for you.

461
00:25:11,867 --> 00:25:14,633
You know, this is your chance
to win, for a change.

462
00:25:14,767 --> 00:25:17,933
Represent the oppressed children
of mistresses.
